From a2fedab37416a4c78f9df0e6edd214e9a1bcc7af Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 10:04:43 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Stage 1: unify location data (country/city) across the app

- New src/data/locations.js: single COUNTRIES source (54 African
  countries + starter international set), stable ISO codes, city
  lists, and normalizeLegacyCountry() for backward compatibility.
- New src/components/LocationPicker.jsx: reusable two-step
  country -> city selector with an "Autre ville" free-text fallback.
- New src/hooks/useMediaQuery.js: matchMedia hook + breakpoints,
  foundation for the upcoming responsive Network redesign.
- Wire LocationPicker into signup, profile settings (new fields),
  the Client modal, the Network profile editor, and the Action
  Rapide (quick_posts) publish form. Remove the old PAYS/PAYS_FLAGS/
  VILLES_VIS/AR_VILLES hardcoded, inconsistent lists and dead code.
- Supabase: add clients.city and quick_posts.country columns, and
  normalize the 58 legacy clients.country values (full flag strings)
  to ISO codes to match every other table.
